summary: An Ordinance providing for the payment of the cost and expense of changing and establishing of the curb grades of Sixteenth Avenue Northwest, between West Sixty-fifth Street and West Sixty-seventh Street, and of West Sixty-fifth Street, between Fifteenth Avenue Northwest and Seventeenth Avenue Northwest, as provided for in Ordinance No. 32291 as amended by Ordinance No. 33556 of the City of Seattle, by the issuance and sale of bonds of the district created to pay therefor.
